So a quick overview about Open Beta for Google Play.

44
00:02:14,662 --> 00:02:18,286
So in the past, Open Beta used to be treated as a test market.

45
00:02:18,286 --> 00:02:20,248
It's really, really important that you

46
00:02:20,248 --> 00:02:21,289
don't continue to do this.

47
00:02:21,289 --> 00:02:24,191
If you need to do bug testing, you

48
00:02:24,191 --> 00:02:26,814
need to make sure in-app purchases or ads are working.

49
00:02:26,814 --> 00:02:29,477
Do a larger closed beta on Google Play

50
00:02:29,477 --> 00:02:31,419
and get users in to make sure that it's stable.

51
00:02:32,099 --> 00:02:37,002
The reason why is that the users that you can generate in Open Beta are significant

52
00:02:37,002 --> 00:02:40,624
in terms of both the volume but also the value that they drive.

53
00:02:40,624 --> 00:02:46,708
So wasting those users on a game that either isn't stable or you're not quite sure about

54
00:02:46,708 --> 00:02:48,209
monetization and retention.

55
00:02:48,734 --> 00:02:51,516
or your ads aren't particularly working well,

56
00:02:51,516 --> 00:02:52,998
is a huge missed opportunity.

57
00:02:52,998 --> 00:02:56,701
Open beta is a really important period for Iron Horse games.

58
00:02:56,701 --> 00:02:57,441
So don't waste it.

59
00:02:57,441 --> 00:02:58,682
The second one is keywords.

60
00:02:58,682 --> 00:03:02,766
Keywords are one of those things that everyone

61
00:03:02,766 --> 00:03:03,827
talks about quite a bit.

62
00:03:03,827 --> 00:03:07,470
And they're really important, particularly in open beta.

63
00:03:07,470 --> 00:03:09,551
And it's a critical part of the strategy.

64
00:03:10,672 --> 00:03:11,232
for Open Beta.

65
00:03:11,232 --> 00:03:12,773
So that's strategy, and I'm going

66
00:03:12,773 --> 00:03:14,893
to walk through each of these steps in turn.

67
00:03:14,893 --> 00:03:18,274
It's the most complicated thing that we're

68
00:03:18,274 --> 00:03:21,795
going to talk about today, but it has a lot of value to it.

69
00:03:21,795 --> 00:03:24,976
So the first is choosing and optimizing the keywords

70
00:03:24,976 --> 00:03:26,816
that you're going to use for your game.

71
00:03:26,816 --> 00:03:28,336
So we'll walk through how you do that.

72
00:03:28,336 --> 00:03:29,997
Then you're going to be marketing your game

73
00:03:29,997 --> 00:03:32,757
to increase organic installs from those keywords.

74
00:03:32,757 --> 00:03:34,198
Specifically, what you're doing is

75
00:03:34,198 --> 00:03:36,718
you're marketing your game to increase rank

76
00:03:36,718 --> 00:03:40,239
on keywords, which then generate more organic installs.

77
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:44,421
And then you're compiling all these results together

78
00:03:44,421 --> 00:03:48,063
to make a pitch to Google Play for featuring in early access.

79
00:03:48,063 --> 00:03:50,984
And for folks who don't know, in open beta

80
00:03:50,984 --> 00:03:53,166
there is a feature that you can get,

81
00:03:53,166 --> 00:03:55,627
and it's an early access collection.

82
00:03:55,627 --> 00:03:58,368
So it's a list of games that the Google Play team

83
00:03:58,368 --> 00:04:00,249
is deemed worthy of featuring.

84
00:04:00,249 --> 00:04:03,071
So you get significantly increased exposure and installs

85
00:04:03,071 --> 00:04:03,711
as a result of it.

86
00:04:03,711 --> 00:04:05,772
But the important thing is you have

87
00:04:05,772 --> 00:04:08,213
to make a case as to why they should feature the game

88
00:04:08,213 --> 00:04:08,773
and support you.

89
00:04:10,260 --> 00:04:14,205
So how many installs can you get from ASL?

90
00:04:14,205 --> 00:04:17,289
On a title that had no early access feature,

91
00:04:17,289 --> 00:04:18,551
7,000 out of my 13,000 installs

92
00:04:18,551 --> 00:04:21,955
that came into the game organically in a month

93
00:04:21,955 --> 00:04:22,576
came from search traffic.

94
00:04:22,576 --> 00:04:25,520
On a title that did have an early access feature,

95
00:04:25,520 --> 00:04:26,902
15,000 out of 31,000 organic installs

96
00:04:26,902 --> 00:04:29,004
came into the game in a month.

97
00:04:30,329 --> 00:04:33,332
What's important to note here is the volumes aren't, I mean,

98
00:04:33,332 --> 00:04:37,356
they're nothing to write home about yet, but the quality is.

99
00:04:37,356 --> 00:04:42,201
Search and ASO installs are the most valuable users

100
00:04:42,201 --> 00:04:45,405
that I've acquired in my game in open beta.

101
00:04:45,405 --> 00:04:47,507
So they are every bit as valuable as users

102
00:04:47,507 --> 00:04:50,630
that I've acquired via user acquisition,

103
00:04:50,630 --> 00:04:52,412
and they're significantly more valuable.

104
00:04:53,549 --> 00:04:59,554
than organic users, particularly when you start looking at early access featuring, which

105
00:04:59,554 --> 00:05:00,795
means you get a lot more traffic.

106
00:05:00,795 --> 00:05:06,540
So talking about the steps of how to actually do this, the first one is choosing your keywords.

107
00:05:06,540 --> 00:05:07,942
This one's pretty basic.

108
00:05:07,942 --> 00:05:13,506
When you're trying to figure out which keywords to use, I typically use a combination of common

109
00:05:13,506 --> 00:05:15,848
sense and then also look at what my competitors are doing.

110
00:05:16,624 --> 00:05:18,246
So from a common sense perspective,

111
00:05:18,246 --> 00:05:19,749
if you have a tower defense game,

112
00:05:19,749 --> 00:05:22,133
there's a pretty good chance that you want

113
00:05:22,133 --> 00:05:24,397
two of your keywords to be tower and defense,

114
00:05:24,397 --> 00:05:25,038
tower defense combined.

115
00:05:25,038 --> 00:05:26,661
I know it's a shocking revelation,

116
00:05:26,661 --> 00:05:30,026
but those are some keywords that you should chase after.

117
00:05:31,351 --> 00:05:35,795
Figuring out which keywords are good is a whole other matter entirely, and this requires

118
00:05:35,795 --> 00:05:37,436
quite a bit of trial and error.

119
00:05:37,436 --> 00:05:41,119
So you can use SensorTower, and I use SensorTower, and there are a number of tools out there

120
00:05:41,119 --> 00:05:42,160
that are free.

121
00:05:42,160 --> 00:05:44,543
SensorTower is free up to a certain point.

122
00:05:44,543 --> 00:05:49,027
But essentially what they do is they give you an approximation of the amount of traffic

123
00:05:49,027 --> 00:05:51,309
that you can get from a particular keyword.

124
00:05:52,029 --> 00:05:54,111
And then it can also show you the difficulty.

125
00:05:54,111 --> 00:05:58,035
So if it's a nine or above, it's going to be really challenging to get a, to rank in

126
00:05:58,035 --> 00:05:59,276
that keyword.

127
00:05:59,276 --> 00:06:02,319
Um, typically from a traffic perspective, you want to be five, six, seven.

128
00:06:02,319 --> 00:06:03,780
It's usually a pretty good rate there.

129
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:09,125
You also want to be choosing three to five different keywords to focus on.

130
00:06:09,125 --> 00:06:11,107
Um, the reason is a little depressing.

131
00:06:11,107 --> 00:06:13,730
It's because most of your keywords aren't going to work.

132
00:06:13,930 --> 00:06:19,713
The reality of it is each game's a little bit different,

133
00:06:19,713 --> 00:06:22,294
and when somebody's searching tower defense,

134
00:06:22,294 --> 00:06:25,035
they may not choose your game based solely on the icon

135
00:06:25,035 --> 00:06:27,937
or some strange thing that you did with the title,

136
00:06:27,937 --> 00:06:29,077
so you need to hedge your bets

137
00:06:29,077 --> 00:06:30,938
and have a couple keywords that you're focusing on.

138
00:06:32,259 --> 00:06:34,921
because most of them aren't going to work out.

139
00:06:34,921 --> 00:06:36,662
So optimizing your keywords,

140
00:06:36,662 --> 00:06:39,604
this one has required a lot of trial and error on my part,

141
00:06:39,604 --> 00:06:41,485
and it's something that I'm pretty proud

142
00:06:41,485 --> 00:06:43,727
to have figured out some small element of.

143
00:06:43,727 --> 00:06:47,889
So keywords are composed of kind of a keyword bank.

144
00:06:47,889 --> 00:06:51,432
So your bundle ID, description, short description,

145
00:06:51,432 --> 00:06:54,073
title and subtitle all form a word bank, right?

146
00:06:54,073 --> 00:06:56,275
And your keywords are pulled from that word bank.

147
00:06:57,158 --> 00:06:59,140
And what you want to be focusing here on

148
00:06:59,140 --> 00:07:02,122
is not the number of times you're mentioning a keyword,

149
00:07:02,122 --> 00:07:05,904
but the density of that keyword relative to the overall number

150
00:07:05,904 --> 00:07:07,805
of words in your description.

151
00:07:07,805 --> 00:07:11,067
For instance, this is my game on Civil War below.

152
00:07:11,067 --> 00:07:15,010
And the word card has a density of 3%.

153
00:07:15,010 --> 00:07:19,212
It's like 3% of all words in that keyword bank.

154
00:07:20,513 --> 00:07:23,934
is card.

155
00:07:23,934 --> 00:07:25,315
And the reason for that is I really

156
00:07:25,315 --> 00:07:27,576
want people searching card to find my game.

157
00:07:27,576 --> 00:07:29,937
App Tweak is the tool I use for this.

158
00:07:29,937 --> 00:07:31,678
This is a free tool.

159
00:07:31,678 --> 00:07:33,978
They have a keyword density tool that's really great.

160
00:07:33,978 --> 00:07:36,059
You can also see which keyword density

161
00:07:36,059 --> 00:07:39,741
your competitors are using to figure things out.

162
00:07:39,741 --> 00:07:41,942
So this step is split into two phases,

163
00:07:41,942 --> 00:07:43,062
and I've done both.

164
00:07:43,062 --> 00:07:44,963
So the first step, if you're fortunate enough

165
00:07:44,963 --> 00:07:46,904
to be in this position, is how you do marketing

166
00:07:46,904 --> 00:07:47,524
when you have money.

167
00:07:48,155 --> 00:07:50,757
The second step, which is the reality for a lot of folks

168
00:07:50,757 --> 00:07:52,218
who are starting out marketing, is

169
00:07:52,218 --> 00:07:54,761
how you market when you don't have any money.

170
00:07:54,761 --> 00:07:57,183
Both are pretty interesting for different reasons.

171
00:07:57,183 --> 00:08:00,106
The first thing you want to do is get an attribution partner

172
00:08:00,106 --> 00:08:01,127
in the game.

173
00:08:01,127 --> 00:08:03,969
This is an SDK that tracks where your installs are coming from

174
00:08:03,969 --> 00:08:04,810
and helps assign value.

175
00:08:04,810 --> 00:08:09,394
These are all mostly the same these days.

176
00:08:09,394 --> 00:08:12,017
Adjust, Coachava, AppsFlyer, they all more or less

177
00:08:12,017 --> 00:08:12,517
offer.

178
00:08:13,038 --> 00:08:14,039
The same types of services.

179
00:08:14,039 --> 00:08:16,863
The key difference is the level of service

180
00:08:16,863 --> 00:08:18,686
that you get from the partner

181
00:08:18,686 --> 00:08:21,129
relative to the size of your business.

182
00:08:21,129 --> 00:08:23,512
So for me, when I started, I was a very small business.

183
00:08:23,512 --> 00:08:25,756
I'm used to being ignored when you're a small business.

184
00:08:25,756 --> 00:08:27,458
I think folks can relate to that.

185
00:08:27,458 --> 00:08:29,301
That never happened with AppsFlyer.

186
00:08:30,140 --> 00:08:34,722
very basic questions, they would always answer it as if I were a million-dollar partner.

187
00:08:34,722 --> 00:08:36,944
I'm paying them a huge amount of money.

188
00:08:36,944 --> 00:08:38,505
So I can't endorse them strongly enough.

189
00:08:38,505 --> 00:08:40,566
I think AppSolar is great.

190
00:08:40,566 --> 00:08:42,927
I use Facebook and Unity to start my campaigns.

191
00:08:42,927 --> 00:08:44,888
There are a couple reasons for this.

192
00:08:44,888 --> 00:08:48,010
One, the traffic is high quality, and two, it's under your control.

193
00:08:48,010 --> 00:08:51,252
You don't have to talk to anybody at Facebook or Unity to kick these campaigns off.

194
00:08:51,252 --> 00:08:52,293
You can just do it yourself.

195
00:08:52,693 --> 00:08:56,976
And with AppsFlyer, you don't have to put in the Unity or Facebook SDKs or any of that

196
00:08:56,976 --> 00:08:57,757
stuff.

197
00:08:57,757 --> 00:09:01,220
You can just put AppsFlyer in and that takes care of the attribution piece for you.

198
00:09:01,220 --> 00:09:06,244
Typically you're spending $50 to $100 a day, so you're not breaking the bank here to acquire

199
00:09:06,244 --> 00:09:07,365
these users.

200
00:09:07,365 --> 00:09:09,286
Targeting should really be focused.

201
00:09:09,286 --> 00:09:13,790
One, you can only do targeting on Facebook at the start, and then two, it should really

202
00:09:13,790 --> 00:09:17,293
be focused around the types of users that are in the genre of game that you're working

203
00:09:17,293 --> 00:09:17,333
on.

204
00:09:17,922 --> 00:09:20,923
I focus on tier one markets for my games,

205
00:09:20,923 --> 00:09:22,264
depending on the audience you appeal to.

206
00:09:22,264 --> 00:09:23,385
You may wanna change that up,

207
00:09:23,385 --> 00:09:27,046
but for me that's US, UK, Germany, France,

208
00:09:27,046 --> 00:09:28,787
Canada, and Australia.

209
00:09:30,268 --> 00:09:32,810
So how do you market without any money?

210
00:09:32,810 --> 00:09:34,291
There are two ways to do it.

211
00:09:34,291 --> 00:09:36,713
In my experience, I've done them both.

212
00:09:36,713 --> 00:09:39,755
The first one is you can get an integration bonus.

213
00:09:39,755 --> 00:09:40,875
So this can be anywhere from $5,000 to $20,000

214
00:09:40,875 --> 00:09:42,016
from an ad partner.

215
00:09:42,016 --> 00:09:45,498
The way that this works, and it's complicated,

216
00:09:45,498 --> 00:09:46,879
is you go to the ad partner and say,

217
00:09:46,879 --> 00:09:47,820
I want to put your ads in the game.

218
00:09:47,820 --> 00:09:49,681
And they're like, great, here's the SDK.

219
00:09:49,681 --> 00:09:52,563
You say, not so fast, give me $20,000.

220
00:09:52,563 --> 00:09:52,943
And they say, OK.

221
00:09:52,943 --> 00:09:58,447
The reality of the situation is the conversation

222
00:09:58,447 --> 00:10:00,088
is actually very close to that.

223
00:10:00,704 --> 00:10:05,728
Ask for some advertising credits, and typically you can get anywhere from $5,000 to $20,000

224
00:10:05,728 --> 00:10:10,792
in free advertising just for getting their SDK in the game and showing off your ads.

225
00:10:10,792 --> 00:10:14,676
If you have any kind of background in games, they're usually jumping at the chance, and

226
00:10:14,676 --> 00:10:18,039
they really care about getting new partners to integrate their ads.

227
00:10:18,039 --> 00:10:19,260
So there's no harm in asking.

228
00:10:19,260 --> 00:10:20,040
If they say no...

229
00:10:20,565 --> 00:10:22,227
move on to the next partner and ask them.

230
00:10:22,227 --> 00:10:24,569
The second way to do this, and again,

231
00:10:24,569 --> 00:10:25,870
this is gonna be really complicated,

232
00:10:25,870 --> 00:10:27,712
is getting a line of credit from marketing partners.

233
00:10:27,712 --> 00:10:30,074
Again, the way that this one works,

234
00:10:30,074 --> 00:10:33,177
is you say, hey, I want a line of credit.

235
00:10:33,177 --> 00:10:34,859
And they say, okay.

236
00:10:34,859 --> 00:10:38,042
And then you get a line of credit

237
00:10:38,042 --> 00:10:38,702
for either 50 or $100,000.

238
00:10:38,702 --> 00:10:40,904
The key with a line of credit

239
00:10:40,904 --> 00:10:43,026
is you have to pay that money back.

240
00:10:43,267 --> 00:10:45,348
So be careful, because anything you spend,

241
00:10:45,348 --> 00:10:47,530
you're going to have to pay back for them.

242
00:10:47,530 --> 00:10:51,234
I've had lines of credit extended through five marketing

243
00:10:51,234 --> 00:10:55,998
partners with no background or credit checks

244
00:10:55,998 --> 00:10:58,140
for a total of a few million dollars.

245
00:10:58,140 --> 00:11:02,464
It's as simple as asking for it.

246
00:11:04,427 --> 00:11:06,128
So from this step, once you have your marketing going

247
00:11:06,128 --> 00:11:09,151
on Facebook and Unity, you can start monitoring your keywords.

248
00:11:09,151 --> 00:11:10,733
So something really great happened

249
00:11:10,733 --> 00:11:12,494
on the Google Play Developer Console last year

250
00:11:12,494 --> 00:11:13,936
that I think a lot of people missed.

251
00:11:13,936 --> 00:11:16,278
You can actually see how many search installs

252
00:11:16,278 --> 00:11:19,781
you're getting out of your total organics.

