00:11:19,781 --> 00:11:22,104
So if you go to the Dev Console and User Acquisition

254
00:11:22,104 --> 00:11:25,807
and look at Search, you can see the total number of installs.

255
00:11:25,807 --> 00:11:27,649
Look at the red arrow, and you should be able to see it.

256
00:11:27,809 --> 00:11:29,730
So the things that you're looking for here

257
00:11:29,730 --> 00:11:31,551
are volume and quality.

258
00:11:31,551 --> 00:11:34,773
So if your volume isn't looking like the volume

259
00:11:34,773 --> 00:11:37,295
that I quoted in an earlier slide,

260
00:11:37,295 --> 00:11:39,717
there are two things that are wrong.

261
00:11:39,717 --> 00:11:43,179
So one is you need more user acquisition

262
00:11:43,179 --> 00:11:45,740
to be able to chart in a particular keyword,

263
00:11:45,740 --> 00:11:49,223
or that keyword is not resonating with your game.

264
00:11:49,223 --> 00:11:51,104
So using the tower defense example,

265
00:11:51,104 --> 00:11:53,745
if you have a game that's about tower defense,

266
00:11:53,745 --> 00:11:56,227
but the icon looks like it's a casual match three,

267
00:11:56,487 --> 00:11:58,250
There's going to be a lot of cognitive dissonance

268
00:11:58,250 --> 00:11:59,892
for people searching, and they're probably

269
00:11:59,892 --> 00:12:00,974
not going to download your game.

270
00:12:00,974 --> 00:12:03,418
So you want that to be a holistic package

271
00:12:03,418 --> 00:12:07,644
with the title, screenshots, and icon reinforcing what

272
00:12:07,644 --> 00:12:09,087
the genre of the game is about.

273
00:12:10,160 --> 00:12:14,481
If you're having quality issues, you need to change keywords.

274
00:12:14,481 --> 00:12:16,062
Different keywords have different qualities.

275
00:12:16,062 --> 00:12:19,203
So I've seen keywords with very low ARPUs

276
00:12:19,203 --> 00:12:20,983
driving users in the game.

277
00:12:20,983 --> 00:12:22,524
I've seen keywords with very high ARPUs

278
00:12:22,524 --> 00:12:24,664
driving users in the game.

279
00:12:24,664 --> 00:12:26,445
This is trial and error.

280
00:12:26,445 --> 00:12:28,445
And really looking at what competitors are doing

281
00:12:28,445 --> 00:12:29,566
for leg up here as well.

282
00:12:30,266 --> 00:12:35,569
Troubleshooting is either changing keywords, increasing your marketing, or

283
00:12:35,569 --> 00:12:40,331
mixing around the density to increase density on a particular keyword. I always

284
00:12:40,331 --> 00:12:44,473
target the top 10 or 15 in terms of a keyword. It's attainable, it's easy, it

285
00:12:44,473 --> 00:12:48,895
generates organic installs and those organic installs are really valuable.

286
00:12:50,034 --> 00:12:53,657
So once you've got your keyword installs floating in,

287
00:12:53,657 --> 00:12:55,438
and you have marketing going, you're

288
00:12:55,438 --> 00:12:56,779
also going to apply for early access.

289
00:12:56,779 --> 00:12:59,522
So this is kind of the culmination

290
00:12:59,522 --> 00:13:01,643
of the open beta process.

291
00:13:01,643 --> 00:13:04,125
Google's a business, and what they care about

292
00:13:04,125 --> 00:13:06,007
is return on investment for their investment.

293
00:13:06,227 --> 00:13:10,049
So when they're thinking about where they're going to put their features, what they're

294
00:13:10,049 --> 00:13:14,991
really choosing is like, does Mike have the game with the highest RPU this week?

295
00:13:14,991 --> 00:13:18,333
And is he supporting it as fully as these other partners are?

296
00:13:18,333 --> 00:13:22,735
So they're making a differentiation between you and other partners in your competing.

297
00:13:22,735 --> 00:13:24,196
So you need to make that case.

298
00:13:24,196 --> 00:13:25,596
And the case really needs to be around.

299
00:13:26,197 --> 00:13:30,698
the support that you're giving the game from a marketing

300
00:13:30,698 --> 00:13:33,559
perspective, the growth that you've seen and driven

301
00:13:33,559 --> 00:13:36,000
on your own, but also the potential.

302
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:36,760
So far, our pool is $0.50.

303
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:37,900
If we had another 50,000 installs,

304
00:13:37,900 --> 00:13:40,961
that would be a great business for both of us.

305
00:13:40,961 --> 00:13:41,661
So make that case.

306
00:13:41,661 --> 00:13:43,822
Don't be shy about talking about the efforts

307
00:13:43,822 --> 00:13:45,483
that you made to grow the game to that point.

308
00:13:45,483 --> 00:13:47,943
Google will listen.

309
00:13:47,943 --> 00:13:49,504
So moving on to the launch step.

310
00:13:49,504 --> 00:13:51,264
This is probably the most important part

311
00:13:51,264 --> 00:13:52,405
of the presentation today.

312
00:13:52,405 --> 00:13:54,285
It's the one you should pay the closest attention to.

313
00:13:55,651 --> 00:13:57,832
This window lasts 30 days.

314
00:13:57,832 --> 00:14:02,195
And it begins the moment that you push from open beta

315
00:14:02,195 --> 00:14:02,795
to production.

316
00:14:02,795 --> 00:14:06,897
During this time, your organic to paid ratios

317
00:14:06,897 --> 00:14:09,339
are going to be incredibly inflated,

318
00:14:09,339 --> 00:14:11,380
the most inflated you've ever seen for the game

319
00:14:11,380 --> 00:14:12,481
and will ever see for the game.

320
00:14:12,901 --> 00:14:16,205
So this can be as high as four organic installs

321
00:14:16,205 --> 00:14:17,287
for every paid install.

322
00:14:17,287 --> 00:14:19,069
And this is without a feature.

323
00:14:19,069 --> 00:14:21,331
So forget about features for the moment.

324
00:14:21,331 --> 00:14:24,315
We're talking about if you buy one install,

325
00:14:24,315 --> 00:14:26,077
you're generating three to four installs

326
00:14:26,077 --> 00:14:27,499
organically in this first 30-day window.

327
00:14:29,103 --> 00:14:31,965
So for me, this is one below where we spent lightly,

328
00:14:31,965 --> 00:14:34,606
and it was a one to two ratio for the first 30 days.

329
00:14:34,606 --> 00:14:38,528
So the launch strategy here is much simpler.

330
00:14:38,528 --> 00:14:40,448
You wanna spend money in the first 30 days,

331
00:14:40,448 --> 00:14:43,250
and you wanna spend as much as you possibly can

332
00:14:43,250 --> 00:14:44,910
to generate as many organics as you can.

333
00:14:45,533 --> 00:14:47,354
Apple is a little bit different.

334
00:14:47,354 --> 00:14:49,495
So when you spend, you move up on charts,

335
00:14:49,495 --> 00:14:51,315
and it increases visibility.

336
00:14:51,315 --> 00:14:54,096
On Google, when you spend, it increases visibility

337
00:14:54,096 --> 00:14:55,816
through the lists in the stores.

338
00:14:55,816 --> 00:14:59,498
So all the lists that you're seeing here

339
00:14:59,498 --> 00:15:03,159
are where you're going to see your games icon populated.

340
00:15:03,159 --> 00:15:05,779
And it can generate a significant amount of installs.

341
00:15:05,779 --> 00:15:06,480
How many installs?

342
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:10,841
So this is averaged across multiple titles.

343
00:15:10,841 --> 00:15:12,661
Acquired 75,000 installs on average,

344
00:15:12,661 --> 00:15:15,222
generated 175,000 installs organically.

345
00:15:16,241 --> 00:15:19,383
without any feature from Google Play.

346
00:15:19,383 --> 00:15:21,305
The cost of those 75,000 installs

347
00:15:21,305 --> 00:15:24,167
is obviously variable depending on the strategy

348
00:15:24,167 --> 00:15:25,888
that you're using.

349
00:15:25,888 --> 00:15:27,369
But you can get that for as low as $25,000

350
00:15:27,369 --> 00:15:30,411
if you're really scrappy with your install sources.

351
00:15:30,411 --> 00:15:35,314
Step one, and this is the most important step,

352
00:15:35,314 --> 00:15:38,076
is you need to learn from open beta.

353
00:15:38,076 --> 00:15:40,357
If you're going to spend $25,000 or even $75,000

354
00:15:40,357 --> 00:15:42,879
on paid user acquisition in the launch window,

355
00:15:43,412 --> 00:15:44,932
you need to know what you're doing.

356
00:15:44,932 --> 00:15:47,033
And the best way to learn is in open beta.

357
00:15:47,033 --> 00:15:50,795
So figure out which marketing creative was best for you,

358
00:15:50,795 --> 00:15:54,256
which channels and targeting had the highest ROI.

359
00:15:54,256 --> 00:15:56,637
So this is really important, I think.

360
00:15:56,637 --> 00:15:59,539
When you talk about open beta and think about testing,

361
00:15:59,539 --> 00:16:01,160
there actually is one thing you wanna be testing,

362
00:16:01,160 --> 00:16:03,100
and that's for marketing creative and strategy.

363
00:16:03,100 --> 00:16:05,061
And you wanna be rock solid on that

364
00:16:05,061 --> 00:16:06,842
before you move on to this phase.

365
00:16:06,842 --> 00:16:08,703
You also wanna be decently capitalized,

366
00:16:08,703 --> 00:16:11,264
so don't spend all that money that you make in open beta.

367
00:16:12,443 --> 00:16:15,026
You also want to make sure that your keyword's in good shape

368
00:16:15,026 --> 00:16:17,108
for launch because those can be significant contributors

369
00:16:17,108 --> 00:16:17,889
of traffic as well.

370
00:16:17,889 --> 00:16:20,671
Step two is choosing your marketing partners.

371
00:16:20,671 --> 00:16:23,434
So for me, my two main partners are Unity and Facebook.

372
00:16:23,434 --> 00:16:26,097
I also use Tapjoy and IronSource.

373
00:16:26,097 --> 00:16:29,100
Unity and Facebook are self-service and great.

374
00:16:29,100 --> 00:16:30,562
You need a little bit of help on setup

375
00:16:30,562 --> 00:16:32,624
with Tapjoy and IronSource, but the quality is great.

376
00:16:33,545 --> 00:16:37,066
So I'm going to go through Unity and Facebook in detail with some tips,

377
00:16:37,066 --> 00:16:38,666
but first some facts.

378
00:16:38,666 --> 00:16:41,667
On Unity, it's not going to exceed your budget or your bid.

379
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:44,587
So this is actually really great if you're doing scrappy marketing

380
00:16:44,587 --> 00:16:48,808
because you'll wake up one day and instead of blowing the budget out

381
00:16:48,808 --> 00:16:51,509
and having overspent doing user acquisition,

382
00:16:51,509 --> 00:16:53,149
your traffic will just disappear, right?

383
00:16:53,149 --> 00:16:55,110
So your bids won't go up.

384
00:16:55,430 --> 00:16:57,592
they will just disappear entirely.

385
00:16:57,592 --> 00:16:59,294
It only uses video creatives,

386
00:16:59,294 --> 00:17:00,875
so it's important to get as many of those

387
00:17:00,875 --> 00:17:01,916
generated as possible.

388
00:17:01,916 --> 00:17:04,319
I typically have three to four different video ads

389
00:17:04,319 --> 00:17:05,740
that I'm running on a per game basis,

390
00:17:05,740 --> 00:17:08,343
and they don't have to be wildly different, right?

391
00:17:08,343 --> 00:17:10,145
You don't need custom, different video ads.

392
00:17:10,145 --> 00:17:12,227
You can do slight variations.

393
00:17:12,788 --> 00:17:14,370
And you can get a line of credit from Unity.

394
00:17:14,370 --> 00:17:16,472
They're really great to work with in that regard.

395
00:17:16,472 --> 00:17:16,993
So some tips.

396
00:17:16,993 --> 00:17:21,258
These are things that have cost a decent amount of money

397
00:17:21,258 --> 00:17:21,879
for me to learn.

398
00:17:21,879 --> 00:17:23,320
Hopefully they're helpful to you.

399
00:17:23,320 --> 00:17:26,665
So blind bidding around your ARPU.

400
00:17:26,665 --> 00:17:29,668
In the launch window, you have such an increased volume

401
00:17:29,668 --> 00:17:32,291
of organic installs as a result of your marketing.

402
00:17:32,772 --> 00:17:37,355
that you want to be driving as much paid acquisition as you can.

403
00:17:37,355 --> 00:17:39,356
So blind bidding is a great way to do that.

404
00:17:39,356 --> 00:17:42,678
So if you have a $0.50 ARPU from Unity users,

405
00:17:42,678 --> 00:17:48,562
and you know that from Open Beta, you may be able to drive,

406
00:17:48,562 --> 00:17:51,164
let's say, 10 installs at that $0.50 bid, right?

407
00:17:51,164 --> 00:17:53,145
You may find that if you bid a little bit lower,

408
00:17:53,145 --> 00:17:55,967
so blind bid down by $0.10, see what happens.

409
00:17:55,967 --> 00:17:57,328
Maybe it's the same.

410
00:17:57,328 --> 00:17:58,609
Maybe you get 50 installs for that.

411
00:17:58,709 --> 00:18:03,711
What I've found is that if you increase that bid to 75 cents, 80 cents, 90 cents, you can

412
00:18:03,711 --> 00:18:05,192
see multiples of installs.

413
00:18:05,192 --> 00:18:12,234
So there are these kind of weird hidden trip lines on Unity around bids that can unleash

414
00:18:12,234 --> 00:18:18,036
way, way larger volumes of traffic than what you would see if you just bid around your

415
00:18:18,036 --> 00:18:18,197
RPO.

416
00:18:18,197 --> 00:18:21,518
And you may make that calculation in your head to say, you know what?

417
00:18:22,799 --> 00:18:28,423
It's better for me to lose 10 cents on a user during the launch window if I'm driving

418
00:18:28,423 --> 00:18:31,966
three or four organic installs for every user.

419
00:18:31,966 --> 00:18:34,028
Like you're comfortable with that trade-off.

420
00:18:34,028 --> 00:18:38,252
But the only way to know is really to play around with that bid per geo, particularly

421
00:18:38,252 --> 00:18:38,732
in the US.

422
00:18:39,935 --> 00:18:41,496
Slight creative variations.

423
00:18:41,496 --> 00:18:43,618
So one of the things that most people

424
00:18:43,618 --> 00:18:45,840
who are doing paid user acquisition struggle with

425
00:18:45,840 --> 00:18:47,061
is a rise in CPI.

426
00:18:47,061 --> 00:18:50,424
I mean, this is natural.

427
00:18:50,424 --> 00:18:53,287
People are getting exposed to your ads.

428
00:18:53,287 --> 00:18:55,829
They're being less, they become less inclined

429
00:18:55,829 --> 00:18:57,591
to download them if they pass on your ad creative

430
00:18:57,591 --> 00:18:58,592
the first time through.

431
00:18:58,592 --> 00:19:00,454
A great way to fight against this

432
00:19:00,454 --> 00:19:02,415
isn't to increase your bid, it's to add new creative.

433
00:19:02,415 --> 00:19:04,958
Even if that creative performs poorly

434
00:19:04,958 --> 00:19:06,419
relative to your main.

435
00:19:06,779 --> 00:19:12,486
video, adding new creative artificially triggers Unity's system to give you an impression

436
00:19:12,486 --> 00:19:12,886
bump.

437
00:19:12,886 --> 00:19:15,049
Because from Unity's perspective, what they're saying is...

438
00:19:15,524 --> 00:19:16,985
Well, I'm going to give this ad a good shot.

439
00:19:16,985 --> 00:19:19,325
They don't know if it's a bad ad or not yet.

440
00:19:19,325 --> 00:19:21,666
They have to give you enough impressions to figure it out.

441
00:19:21,666 --> 00:19:23,807
So put up new video.

442
00:19:23,807 --> 00:19:25,167
You'll get an impression bump.

443
00:19:25,167 --> 00:19:26,728
You'll keep your bids the same.

444
00:19:26,728 --> 00:19:28,309
And you'll get traffic at the same bid

445
00:19:28,309 --> 00:19:30,870
without having to increase your bids.

446
00:19:30,870 --> 00:19:32,290
I do this a lot.

447
00:19:32,290 --> 00:19:35,711
And I do it with slight variations of my video

448
00:19:35,711 --> 00:19:36,451
creative.

449
00:19:37,137 --> 00:19:42,279
If you do it too much, you're going to hear from your Unity rep and you really should

450
00:19:42,279 --> 00:19:46,741
experiment with your videos, but this is a great way around constantly raising your bits.

451
00:19:46,741 --> 00:19:53,824
Finally share your session and revenue information with Unity because later on they can come

452
00:19:53,824 --> 00:19:59,507
up with some really interesting audience targeting for you that has higher ROI with more or less

453
00:19:59,507 --> 00:20:00,787
the same CPI.

454
00:20:00,787 --> 00:20:03,088
So their Day 7 ROA campaigns are great.

455
00:20:03,929 --> 00:20:05,169
Folks aren't using those.

456
00:20:05,169 --> 00:20:07,591
Unity's got some really advanced targeting stuff

457
00:20:07,591 --> 00:20:09,452
that you should be checking out.

458
00:20:09,452 --> 00:20:10,532
Step two, Facebook.

459
00:20:10,532 --> 00:20:12,493
So they won't exceed your budget,

460
00:20:12,493 --> 00:20:15,655
but boy, they'll exceed your bid.

461
00:20:15,655 --> 00:20:18,717
So if anyone here has spent on Facebook,

462
00:20:18,717 --> 00:20:20,858
you found out that if you go to bed on a Friday

463
00:20:20,858 --> 00:20:22,659
and you're getting users for 10 cents,

464
00:20:22,659 --> 00:20:24,099
you may wake up on a Saturday

465
00:20:24,099 --> 00:20:25,280
if you're doing low-cost bidding

466
00:20:25,280 --> 00:20:26,781
and those users now cost a dollar.

467
00:20:27,559 --> 00:20:31,150
So you have to be very careful, especially with low-cost bidding and the amount of budget

468
00:20:31,150 --> 00:20:34,661
that you're allocating for your campaign so that you don't find yourself quickly underwater.

469
00:20:35,096 --> 00:20:36,557
They use display and video ads.

470
00:20:36,557 --> 00:20:38,158
You can get a line of credit.

471
00:20:38,158 --> 00:20:42,060
The Facebook team has actually been really great to work with

472
00:20:42,060 --> 00:20:44,341
from a small developer standpoint,

473
00:20:44,341 --> 00:20:46,162
even when I was spending significantly less

474
00:20:46,162 --> 00:20:47,682
than I was spending now.

475
00:20:47,682 --> 00:20:48,503
So some tips here.

476
00:20:48,503 --> 00:20:50,944
Facebook's got a honeymoon period.

477
00:20:50,944 --> 00:20:55,546
So when you have a new job, a new girlfriend or boyfriend,

478
00:20:55,546 --> 00:20:57,928
everything is wonderful for the first couple of months.

479
00:20:57,928 --> 00:21:00,109
Then you find out what it's really like.

480
00:21:01,129 --> 00:21:01,970
Facebook's the same way.

481
00:21:01,970 --> 00:21:05,872
So the first two months, you're going to see amazing CPIs.

482
00:21:05,872 --> 00:21:07,773
And in your mind, you're going to say, man,

483
00:21:07,773 --> 00:21:09,614
I'm going to be able to spend four days on Facebook

484
00:21:09,614 --> 00:21:10,034
with $0.20 CPIs.

485
00:21:10,034 --> 00:21:11,015
This is amazing.

486
00:21:11,015 --> 00:21:12,135
That goes away.

487
00:21:12,135 --> 00:21:15,737
So you have a limited period of time

488
00:21:15,737 --> 00:21:17,318
where you're going to get those CPIs.

489
00:21:17,318 --> 00:21:22,621
And once you have run out that clock, you can't go back.

490
00:21:23,121 --> 00:21:28,762
So you want to make sure that you are spending carefully on Facebook, particularly in open

491
00:21:28,762 --> 00:21:34,064
beta because you don't want to run out your honeymoon outside of the launch window.

492
00:21:34,064 --> 00:21:38,465
Another tip, and this is one that I think people miss all the time, display ads are

493
00:21:38,465 --> 00:21:39,465
just fine.

494
00:21:39,465 --> 00:21:43,946
I mean, video ads are really popular, playable ads are really popular.

495
00:21:43,946 --> 00:21:48,507
The bread and butter of my entire business, static display ads.

496
00:21:49,542 --> 00:21:53,625
Most of my advertising on Facebook comes through static display ads. They work just fine.

497
00:21:53,625 --> 00:21:56,888
CTRs are comparable with video ads, CPIs are even less.

498
00:21:56,888 --> 00:22:00,631
They are the workhorse of my marketing campaigns on Facebook.

499
00:22:00,631 --> 00:22:08,298
And another weird one on Facebook is low-cost bidding. So low-cost bidding essentially, I've mentioned it a couple times,

500
00:22:08,298 --> 00:22:11,981
but it's where you allow Facebook to determine what the CPI is going to be for your campaign.

501
00:22:11,981 --> 00:22:14,363
So you allow their algorithm to figure it out for you.

502
00:22:15,074 --> 00:22:18,579
This is great during the honeymoon period and after it, it is not great.

503
00:22:18,579 --> 00:22:20,241
Your CPIs will escalate quickly.

504
00:22:20,241 --> 00:22:24,488
So the strategy for dealing with this, start with a low-cost campaign.

